    _ipc_doc(section='166', title='Public Servant Disobeying Law with Intent to Cause Injury', focus='This section protects lawful administration of justice or public administration by penalising false information, disobedience of legal duty by officials, or perjury-related misconduct. The objective is to preserve integrity of public decision-making and court proceedings.', punishment='The sentence varies by section. Some provisions are primarily definitional, while others prescribe imprisonment and fine, especially where false evidence is used to secure conviction, screen an offender, or injure another person through false accusation.', related='Sections 191 to 200 IPC, Section 201 IPC, Section 211 IPC, Section 340 CrPC, Sections 195 and 196 CrPC restrictions on prosecution, and the law of evidence concerning contradictions and documentary proof', case_law='Perjury and false charge prosecutions are approached cautiously because courts usually insist on clear intentional falsity, materiality of the statement, and compliance with statutory sanction or complaint requirements before taking cognizance.', procedure='the court or competent authority typically records the alleged falsity, considers whether prosecution is expedient in the interests of justice, and then permits complaint or prosecution according to Section 340 CrPC and allied procedural safeguards'),
